{
  "article_id": "Tinsley1901",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "An air of mystery pervades each of",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the little islands",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in the scant archipelago off the coast of",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "California.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Clemente Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scl",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is strewn with enormous prehistoric mortars and pestles, and here and there are numerous evidences that",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a giant race",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "lived there before the Portuguese navigator,",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Cabrillo",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jca",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", sailed for conquest up the coast of",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Alta, Cal.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_upcal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in 1542.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is indented by many strange caves, weird grottoes, where one may see remains of",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a race of fishers and artisans",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "with shells.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "has been the scene of titanic erosions by ice, water, and sand. The grotesque pillars that lift themselves above the island level, the winding caves that twist from the shores into the heart of",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and the roaring gulches and canyons all comprise a spot rich in possibilities for both scientist and dreamer.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is used as a pasturage for thousands of sheep, and it, too, is full of absorbing interest regarding extinct races of",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "aborigines",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_chumash",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The Smithsonian Institution scientists have gathered tons of stone, shell and bone utensils and personal ornaments from",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "But",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "has by far the most abundant evidences of",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a tribe",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "of unusually tall and strong people who must have vanished almost in a night. Of all",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the California archipelago",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "this is the most mysterious.",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Notwithstanding"
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—known on the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Pacific coast",
        "entity_key": "re_paccoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "as"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Channel",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "Islands—are but thirty to fifty miles out in the blues of the ocean, they seldom are visited. Every few years an exploring expedition goes to them for a season of scientific study, but with the exception of"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—a famous summer resort for"
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "pleasure-seekers and anglers—a half-dozen visitors do not land at any of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "once a year. To-day"
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "remain as lonely and desolate as they did long before the first white face sailed up the coast—360 years ago."
      },
      {
        "text": "The races",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "which occupied",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "these islands",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "are as much of a mystery as ever, and so far science is baffled in inquiring what sort of folk",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "these aboriginal settlers",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "were, how they lived, what they believed, and especially how they so suddenly and completely disappeared from the face of the earth.",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The University of California, at Berkeley",
        "entity_key": "in_ucb",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", is about to begin the most thorough exploration ever made of"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which lies sixty miles off the coast of"
      },
      {
        "text": "Ventura",
        "entity_key": "co_ventura",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara counties.",
        "entity_key": "co_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "As far back as the memory of any person in"
      },
      {
        "text": "Southern California",
        "entity_key": "re_socal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "runs hundreds of white skeletons have dotted the valleys and hillsides of"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "Strange utensils of serpentine, sandstone and steatite are found there among the human bones, and",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "its inhabitants",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "have a history so curious that it is difficult of comprehension.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}